We found unique IgG antibody patterns associated with
benign MS. Specifically, benign MS patients showed decreased
antibody reactivity to myelin when compared to EDSS- and
DD-matched groups. In addition, we have previously described
that increased antibody reactivity to heat shock proteins (HSPs)
characterizes relapsing-remitting MS patients and we found a sig-
nificant decrease in HSP-specific antibodies in benign patients.
Since HSP-specific immunity is linked to ongoing
inflammation, our data suggests a decreased inflammatory
response in benign MS. Moreover, since IgG antibodies are T-cell
dependent, decreased myelin-specific IgG antibodies suggest a
reduced antigen specific T-cell response in benign MS. Our find-
ings identify a potential biomarker for benign forms of MS and
identification of the mechanisms responsible for decreased
